Taycie Matthews is a rising star in the world of rodeo, particularly in barrel racing. Born and raised in Arkansas, Matthews has made a name for herself in the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA), with significant earnings and a reputation for skill and determination.

She has been on fire in 2023, clearing over $100,000 in earnings and winning major rodeos like Salinas, California.

Here you can follow Taycie Matthews’ net worth, career earnings, career highlights, relationship status, and more.

About Taycie Matthews

Taycie Matthews hails from Wynne, Arkansas. Her older sister, Jaylie, is also a rodeo competitor, and their mother, Kim, has multiple International Pro Rodeo Association (IPRA) qualifications.

Early Life

From a young age, Matthews was no stranger to rodeo travel. She began her journey in the International Pro Rodeo Association scene at the age of 14, riding a horse named Heavenly Firewater, also known as “Bud The Stud”.

The Matthews family purchased Bud and his twin embryo, Feelin The Firewater, known as “Sis,” as yearlings. Bud hit the rodeo trail with Matthews and took to it immediately, leading to three IPRA qualifications for Taycie.

Professional Career

Matthews’ professional career has been marked by significant achievements. In 2023, she won the College National Finals Rodeo (CNFR) barrel racing champion title, bringing it back to The University of West Alabama.

She also won major rodeos like Salinas, California, and cleared over $100,000 in earnings in the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association.

Her horse, Fame Fire Rocks, also known as “Poprocks,” was voted the 2023 WPRA/AQHA Horse of the Year.

Taycie Matthews’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Taycie Matthews has an estimated net worth of $1 million.

In 2023, she cleared over $100,000 in earnings in the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association. By November 2023, her WPRA season earnings were reported to be $144,161.4.

Career Earnings

Taycie Matthews’s career earnings have been impressive, especially considering her young age. In 2023, she managed to clear over $100,000 in earnings in the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA).

By August 2023, she had already accumulated $101,790 in total earnings. As of October 2023, her regular-season earnings were reported to be $144,161.

In the WPRA Pro Rodeo World Standings of 2023, she was listed with earnings of $144,161.40. Her EquiStat Lifetime Earnings were reported to be $353,270.3. These figures demonstrate Matthews’s significant success in the rodeo arena.

Taycie appears to be single. She prefers to keep her private life away from the spotlight.

She is American.
